this composition.”

21
00:01:55,011 --> 00:01:58,952
And when Svarūp Dāmodar 
hears it

22
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:05,175
he is furious, he is the filter 
before things go to Mahāprabhu,

23
00:02:05,175 --> 00:02:07,387
and this is interesting as well—

24
00:02:07,387 --> 00:02:15,129
although Mahāprabhu is described
the mahā-vadānyāya avatāre—

25
00:02:15,129 --> 00:02:22,215
the most munificent, magnanimous avatar,
incarnation of Lord;

26
00:02:22,215 --> 00:02:28,015
so generous,
so merciful to the fallen

27
00:02:28,015 --> 00:02:33,013
but He cannot tolerate 
apa-siddhānta.

28
00:02:33,013 --> 00:02:36,827
He’s merciful to everyone, 
He is descended

29
00:02:36,827 --> 00:02:43,087
patita-pāvana gaura‒hari,
but if He hears apa-siddhānta—

30
00:02:43,087 --> 00:02:48,436
means the improper representation
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

31
00:02:48,436 --> 00:02:51,015
He’ll become angry,

32
00:02:51,015 --> 00:02:55,067
it will disturb His mood 
and He’ll be angry.

33
00:02:55,067 --> 00:02:58,785
So who’s so generous, so sweet,
and kind, and affectionate …

34
00:02:58,785 --> 00:03:02,035
This will make Him angry?

35
00:03:02,181 --> 00:03:05,181
So it means not to meddle

36
00:03:05,181 --> 00:03:08,871
in the upper world 
with the higher things.

37
00:03:08,871 --> 00:03:11,991
It’s more critical
in the lower stage.

38
00:03:11,991 --> 00:03:14,928
Prabhupād’s example was that 
 

39
00:03:14,928 --> 00:03:21,498
like the child with its feet
on the lap of the mother.

40
00:03:21,498 --> 00:03:24,414
It’s offensive to put your feet 
on someone,

41
00:03:24,414 --> 00:03:26,006
but if a mother is holding 
a little baby

42
00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:29,360
and the baby’s feet
are walking on the mother, 
 

43
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:35,015
that is not offensive, it’s OK,
but we see even in this world

44
00:03:35,015 --> 00:03:41,620
as the children start to grow
they get less lap time

45
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:47,888
and inevitably at a certain stage 
they won’t be touching their mother,

46
00:03:47,888 --> 00:03:52,368
their father, their affectionate 
well wishers with their feet.

47
00:03:52,368 --> 00:03:54,187
It will be intolerable,

48
00:03:54,187 --> 00:03:59,484
and it won’t be good for them
to continue that way.

49
00:03:59,484 --> 00:04:05,873
So Svarūp Dāmodar 
tells that, “Mind it.

50
00:04:05,873 --> 00:04:10,937
You are trying to glorify
Mahāprabhu and Jagannāth

51
00:04:10,937 --> 00:04:14,681
and in the process 
you’re going to hell,

52
00:04:14,681 --> 00:04:20,444
because you’re committing aparādh 
against both of them,

53
00:04:21,284 --> 00:04:25,887
because what you are expressing 
 

54
00:04:25,887 --> 00:04:30,487
it hasn’t descended 
from the higher plane

55
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:34,867
using you as an agent 
for expression and distribution,

56
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:41,668
but rather on the bases 
of your perspective, observations

57
00:04:44,018 --> 00:04:49,026
you are imposing that 
on the higher and that’s an offense.

58
00:04:49,026 --> 00:04:51,994
And that man is mortified,

59
00:04:51,994 --> 00:04:56,014
but Svarūp Dāmodar 
ever so qualified says,

60
00:04:56,014 --> 00:04:59,307
“But, if we take the go deeper
and take

61
00:04:59,307 --> 00:05:04,757
other meanings of this words …”
Then he mercifully converts

62
00:05:04,757 --> 00:05:10,606
what was aparādhic in expression 
into a glorification.

63
00:05:10,606 --> 00:05:13,743
That’s part of the qualifications
of Svarūp Dāmodar.

64
00:05:13,743 --> 00:05:17,202
But interestingly whether
in the role of Svarūp Dāmodar

65
00:05:17,202 --> 00:05:22,951
or Lalitā-sakhī, not allowing 
any disturbance to go.

66
00:05:22,951 --> 00:05:25,520
And thematically, in principle,
what are we learnt?

67
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:28,663
—Not allowing any disturbance
to go into the upper world,

68
00:05:28,663 --> 00:05:30,945
the higher world.

69
00:05:32,315 --> 00:05:34,868
As Śrīla Gurudev,

70
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:38,438
he had such an arrangement 
with Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

71
00:05:38,438 --> 00:05:40,909
Guru Mahārāj is on his veranda
in Nabadwip

72
00:05:40,909 --> 00:05:45,959
and Gurudev moving
on the ground level at the Math,

73
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,889
conducting all the seva,

74
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:52,909
to not allow any disturbance 
to go to Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

75
00:05:52,909 --> 00:05:58,159
So that Śrīla Guru Mahārāj 
can compose the “Prema Dhama Deva Stotram”,

76
00:05:58,159 --> 00:06:03,206
conceive of “The Subjective Evolution 
of Consciousness”,

77
00:06:03,206 --> 00:06:05,534
and “The Golden Volcano of Divine Love”,

78
00:06:05,534 --> 00:06:13,796
and so many other things
that’s Gurudev took the anxiety 
 

79
00:06:13,796 --> 00:06:22,424
and whatever inconvenience
was associated with that sevā,

80
00:06:25,055 --> 00:06:27,345
upon himself.

81
00:06:27,565 --> 00:06:31,826
So that Guru Mahārāj 
could proceed with his divine thinking

82
00:06:31,826 --> 00:06:36,589
